3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for end-to-end learning. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as argumentation mining can be seen as a subtask of information retrieval. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for argumentation mining.
